<header>
<div id="instruction">		
		Read these pieces of advice for IELTS Writing Task 1 and decide which of them are things you should do.
</div>
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/set9.1_02.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  
  <div id="targetquestion">
  <p>1.	What should you do before you write?</p>
  <list class="answerList3">
    <li><a id="t1">Decide which figures are not important enough to mention in your report.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t2">Spend time carefully reading any titles, axes, labels and legends before you start writing.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t3">Spend time looking for the main trends before you start writing.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t4">Spend time planning the most appropriate order in which to present the information.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t5">Plan to leave some time at the end to check your report for mistakes.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t6">Ask questions about anything you have not understood.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t7">Try to remember anything you have read about the subject before.</a></li>
	</list>
  
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  <p>2.	What should you do while you are writing?</p>
  <list class="answerList3">
    <li><a id="t8">Copy the question and use it as your opening sentence.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t9">Divide your report into paragraphs.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t10">End your report with one or two sentences summarising the most important trends.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t11">Include a paragraph with your personal opinions about the topic.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t12">Spend more than 20 minutes on Writing Task 1.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t13">Start writing immediately.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t14">Write a minimum of 150 words.</a></li>
  </list>
  
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  <p>3.	What type of language should you use?</p>
  <list class="answerList3">
    <li><a id="t15">Use a linking word or phrase between every sentence.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t16">Use a range of grammatical structures and vocabulary.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t17">Use contractions.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t18">Use formal language.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t19">Use linking words and phrases between sentences and paragraphs where appropriate.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t20">Vary the way you describe figures by using percentages, fractions and ratios.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t21">Refer to the figures.</a></li>
  </list>
  
  <p class="linespace"></p>
  <p>4.	What should you do with the diagrams, charts, graphs and tables?</p>
	<list class="answerList3">
    <li><a id="t22">Add extra information you may know about the topic but which is not included in the diagram, chart, graph or table.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t23">Always describe charts, graphs and tables from left to right or top to bottom.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t24">Include every figure from the chart, graph or table in your report.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t25">Round figures up or down where appropriate.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t26">Summarise overall trends first and then describe any important specific features.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t27">Write a short introduction briefly explaining what the diagram, chart, graph or table shows.</a></li>
    <li><a id="t28">Speculate on possible reasons for the trends and patterns shown in the chart, graph or table.</a></li>
  </list>
  
